    Figure 2 illustrates our goals.
    It shows two sentences belonging to the articles in Figure 1, and highlights and connects their parallel fragments.
    Although the sentences share some common meaning, each of them has content which is not translated on the other side.
    The English phrase reports the BBC&#8217;s Helen Fawkes in Kiev, as well Proceedings of the 21st International Conference on Computational Linguistics and 44th Annual Meeting of the ACL, pages 81&#8211;88, Sydney, July 2006. c&#65533;2006 Association for Computational Linguistics as the Romanian one De altfel, vorbind inaintea aniversarii have no translation correspondent, either in the other sentence or anywhere in the whole document.
    Since the sentence pair contains so much untranslated text, it is unlikely that any parallel sentence detection method would consider it useful.
